156
00:16:24,956 --> 00:16:27,860
So that's greed, aversion, and delusion.

157
00:16:28,801 --> 00:16:33,886
And that they're fundamentally the base of all unwholesome states.

158
00:16:33,866 --> 00:16:50,339
But the taints, which we're coming to later, of course, tomorrow, the cankers, also called, the hindrances and the fetters, all seem to have similarities, with some being blockages to insight and some being yokes to the worldly states.

159
00:16:50,940 --> 00:16:54,407
The same factors may be in the different groups.

160
00:16:54,386 --> 00:17:02,856
Are the taints generally the same thing as the fetters, or is the different way of looking at these items or considering their arising and passing?

161
00:17:03,518 --> 00:17:08,703
The taints may be cleared to allow stream entry.

162
00:17:08,784 --> 00:17:10,786
That's the first level of insight.

163
00:17:11,887 --> 00:17:19,576
But somehow, I'm sure that I've seen clearing the fetters described as being overcome by the same results.

164
00:17:19,717 --> 00:17:22,420
Are fetters and taints interchangeable?

165
00:17:23,075 --> 00:17:27,094
So this is where we get into these lists you see.

166
00:17:28,541 --> 00:17:33,509
The three or four taints are also called ogre.

167
00:17:33,810 --> 00:17:34,852
They're called floods.

168
00:17:35,393 --> 00:17:39,199
They saturate everything, right?

169
00:17:39,219 --> 00:17:41,303
As an unwholesome saturation.

170
00:17:41,824 --> 00:17:47,953
It's like you're painting in watercolours and you have your first wash and that wash gives the whole painting a feel.

171
00:17:48,453 --> 00:17:53,722
So these taints, these oozings are like...

172
00:17:53,702 --> 00:18:02,455
are these floods, these color washes that are behind everything that we speak, think, say, and do.

173
00:18:03,217 --> 00:18:08,144
They're also called yoga, yokes, because they tie us to the worldly thing.

174
00:18:08,724 --> 00:18:15,474
And as taints, they are referred to their malignancy, their horrible oozings.

175
00:18:15,454 --> 00:18:30,445
Now, the fetters, there's only four of those, by the way, the fetters are a specific group of 10, which tell you which ones go as you go up the four stages of awakening.

176
00:18:31,087 --> 00:18:33,092
And the first three to go are

177
00:18:33,393 --> 00:18:44,736
Doubt in the Buddhist teaching, belief that any form of ritual or practices will actually bring about liberation, although they have their place.

178
00:18:45,016 --> 00:18:49,404
Like, you know, I do the taking refuges and precepts.

179
00:18:49,424 --> 00:18:50,227
They have their place.

180
00:18:50,728 --> 00:18:54,355
But you could do that for an eternity and it wouldn't actually liberate you from suffering.

181
00:18:55,094 --> 00:19:09,398
And the final one is the one we've been addressing, is that insight which undermines, you just get that insight into not-self, into the fact that there's something there which is not changing.

182
00:19:10,200 --> 00:19:13,906
And that's, of course, the Buddha calls it like a flash of lightning.

183
00:19:14,146 --> 00:19:18,654
You've seen it, but it's not been long enough to really be sustained.

184
00:19:20,238 --> 00:19:21,559
It has its effect.

185
00:19:21,681 --> 00:19:23,002
So those are the fetters.

186
00:19:23,523 --> 00:19:29,153
Then you've got defilements and latent tendencies.

187
00:19:29,173 --> 00:19:34,723
So I used to know some of these lists, but happily I've forgotten most of them.

188
00:19:35,505 --> 00:19:36,887
It just waits on the mind, I think.

189
00:19:38,510 --> 00:19:39,833
Let me just go to the...

190
00:19:41,685 --> 00:19:42,146
Where am I?

191
00:19:42,166 --> 00:19:43,888
Kilesa, the defilement.

192
00:19:44,690 --> 00:19:48,635
So you've got, none of these will come as a surprise.

193
00:19:49,517 --> 00:19:52,121
Greed, aversion, delusion.

194
00:19:52,141 --> 00:19:53,403
So there's your three basics.

195
00:19:53,864 --> 00:19:56,488
Then you've got conceit, which is to do with me.

196
00:19:57,890 --> 00:19:59,932
Speculative views, wrong views.

197
00:20:01,134 --> 00:20:02,817
And then you've got skeptical doubt.

198
00:20:03,397 --> 00:20:07,103
So that's the doubt that stops you doing something, yeah?

199
00:20:07,083 --> 00:20:14,967
If you're on the high board wanting to dive into the pond, if you doubt that you can do it or you're too afraid to do it, then you just don't jump, you come down.

200
00:20:15,875 --> 00:20:21,059
Mental torpor, so that's a bit of a hindrance or a defilement.

201
00:20:21,421 --> 00:20:26,365
Restlessness, shamelessness, and lack of moral dread.

202
00:20:27,926 --> 00:20:36,736
When we lose shame and fear of consequences, then really there's nothing much to stop us doing unwholesome things.

203
00:20:37,477 --> 00:20:39,419
So those are known as your defilements.

204
00:20:39,439 --> 00:20:40,779
So they're just a group.

205
00:20:40,799 --> 00:20:43,823
